==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wappened
<hw>Wap"pened</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Waped</er>,
<er>Wapper</er>.]</ety> <def>A word of doubtful meaning used once by
Shakespeare.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This [gold] is it</q>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That makes the <qex>wappen'd</qex> widow wed again.</q>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>It is conjectured by some that it is an error for
<xex>wappered</xex>, meaning tremulous or exhausted.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wapper</ent>⟦br⟧
